Hello Roger,

There is a script to list pending urls here:
https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/Heritrix3+Useful+Scripts#Heritrix3UsefulScripts-listpendingurls

Apparently deleting urls matching a regex is as simple as this:

// groovy
count = job.crawlController.frontier.deleteURIs(&quot;.*&quot;, uriRegex);
rawOut.println count + &quot; uris deleted from frontier&quot;

I added this example to the wiki page above. The first argument to 
deleteURIs() is a regex that matches the queue name, so you can use that 
to make your script run faster if you know it&#39;s only certain queues that 
have urls of interest. (Finding this makes me think there might be a 
simpler way to list urls too, but the script I linked to definitely works.)

Noah

